# Android Studio and ADB Installation Guide

## üìå Android Studio Installation

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Download Android Studio  
- Visit the [official Android Studio website](https://developer.android.com/studio).
- Download the latest version for your operating system.

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Run the Installer  
- Open the downloaded file and follow the setup wizard instructions.
- Choose the recommended settings and proceed with installation.

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Install Necessary SDK Components  
- Launch Android Studio and open the **SDK Manager**.
- Install required SDK components like:
  - **Android SDK**
  - **Platform Tools**
  - **Emulator** (if needed)

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Configure System Environment Variables (if needed)  
- **Windows users**: Add the SDK and platform-tools path to the **System Environment Variables** if not automatically set.

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ Verify Installation  
- Open **Android Studio** and create a sample project to ensure everything works correctly.

