## üìå Minimal ADB and Fastboot Installation

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Download Minimal ADB and Fastboot  
- Get the latest version from an official source, such as:
  - [XDA Developers](https://forum.xda-developers.com/)
  - Other trusted websites.

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Install Minimal ADB  
- Run the setup file and follow the installation steps.
- Choose a suitable installation directory.

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Open ADB Command Prompt  
- Navigate to the installed directory.
- Open a command prompt in that directory and verify ADB is installed using:  
  ```sh
  adb version

üìå Enable USB Debugging on Your Android Device

Open Settings on your Android device.
Navigate to About Phone and tap Build Number seven times to enable Developer Options.
Go to Developer Options and enable USB Debugging.

üìå Connect and Verify ADB

Connect your Android device to the computer using a USB cable.
Open a command prompt in the ADB directory and run:
sh
Copy
Edit
adb devices
If prompted, allow USB debugging on your device.
The device should appear in the list. If not, check drivers and reconnect.


